Happy Friday, All! Some updates on year in college:
I modified that popsels that choose the students who get assigned to each year in college in RNANA: 1,3,4,5,7. The popsels now pick up the year in college for the correct term shown in ROASTAT period status tab.&nbsp;
There are still some students who are currently undergraduate but have graduate admission/enrollment for a future term. Those students will get assigned a 7 for year in college in ROASTAT for a given term even if they're still an undergraduate in that term.
I've created a report to identify these students. I've attached a copy of that&nbsp;report to this email.&nbsp;
To fix these students, we need to change their period year in college in ROASTAT to the correct year for the term, 5, and then Check the 'Banner Year in College Lock' for that term.
Once that is done, the next time year in college is run overnight, the job will pick up the year in college from roastat and set the year in college in rnana to the correct value.&nbsp;
I think we only need to worry about updating ROASTAT year in college for students that are actually registered for classes in the given term. I included a column with enrolled hours on the report.&nbsp; Angie, will you be responsible for running this report on a regular basis and fixing the year in college for these students? Where do you want me to put the report on the WebFOCUS dashboard?
